147
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:50,500
I think section one of the bill is by far the most significant change that we're asking for today.

148
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:57,500
Currently under statute, all of our taxes are assessed interest on a daily basis.

149
00:10:57,500 --> 00:11:12,500
And what that means is that a taxpayer could receive a bill on one day and then it is immediately wrong because the interest is accruing on a daily basis.

150
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:33,000
This bill would allow us to assess interest more like a credit card bill, which is to say that we would send a taxpayer a bill and the dollar value on that bill would be good for up to 30 days.

151
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:43,000
And then if they hit that 30 day, the prior 30 days of interest will appear on their next bill.

152
00:11:43,000 --> 00:12:02,500
So we think this is a pretty taxpayer-friendly change, and it will also ease our administration because we find ourselves either billing or writing off these small balances of interest when taxpayers don't calculate their daily interest rate correctly.

153
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:09,500
